    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-cod-with-tamarind-and-coconut-noodles/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-cod-with-tamarind-and-coconut-noodles/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> medium egg noodles</strong> to a large bowl, cover them with<strong> boiled water</strong> and stir for 10 secs to separate the noodles</p><p>Set aside to soak for 5-6 min</p><p>Drain the<strong> soaked noodles</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-cod-with-tamarind-and-coconut-noodles/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>ground turmeric </strong>to a plate with a handful of <strong>flour</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix until fully combined</p><p>Pat your <strong>fish fillet[s] </strong>dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Place the <strong>fish fillet[s] </strong>onto the floured plate, pressing firmly to coat evenly on both sides \u2013 this is your <strong>coated fish</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-cod-with-tamarind-and-coconut-noodles/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated fish </strong>and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-cod-with-tamarind-and-coconut-noodles/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>tamarind & coconut curry paste </strong>and the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-cod-with-tamarind-and-coconut-noodles/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>and your <strong>soy sauce </strong>with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped green beans </strong>to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until tender and the sauce has thickened slightly</p><p>Once cooked, stir through the <strong>drained noodles </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> tamarind & coconut noodles</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-cod-with-tamarind-and-coconut-noodles/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>tamarind & coconut noodles </strong>in a bowl with the <strong>turmeric fish </strong>on top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
